{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U2Hsn3eaFND3B4jRUusjJg","type":"tool_result","content":"1165\t      // Create new profile if not found\n1166\t      return this.createPlayerProfile(wallet);\n1167\t    },\n1168\t\n1169\t    async getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit = 20, game) {\n1170\t      const effectiveLimit = Math.min(limit, 50);\n1171\t      if (cursor && game) {\n1172\t        const rows = await sql<Transaction[]>`\n1173\t          SELECT * FROM transactions\n1174\t          WHERE wallet = ${wallet} AND id < ${cursor} AND game = ${game}\n1175\t          ORDER BY id DESC\n1176\t          LIMIT ${effectiveLimit}\n1177\t        `;\n1178\t        return rows.map(normalizeTransaction);\n1179\t      }\n1180\t      if (cursor) {\n1181\t        const rows = await sql<Transaction[]>`\n1182\t          SELECT * FROM transactions\n1183\t          WHERE wallet = ${wallet} AND id < ${cursor}\n1184\t          ORDER BY id DESC\n1185\t          LIMIT ${effectiveLimit}\n1186\t        `;\n1187\t        return rows.map(normalizeTransaction);\n1188\t      }\n1189\t      if (game) {\n1190\t        const rows = await sql<Transaction[]>`\n1191\t          SELECT * FROM transactions\n1192\t          WHERE wallet = ${wallet} AND game = ${game}\n1193\t          ORDER BY id DESC\n1194\t          LIMIT ${effectiveLimit}\n1195\t        `;\n1196\t        return rows.map(normalizeTransaction);\n1197\t      }\n1198\t      const rows = await sql<Transaction[]>`\n1199\t        SELECT * FROM transactions\n1200\t        WHERE wallet = ${wallet}\n1201\t        ORDER BY id DESC\n1202\t        LIMIT ${effectiveLimit}\n1203\t      `;\n1204\t      return rows.map(normalizeTransaction);\n1205\t    },\n1206\t\n1207\t    async getTransactionsByUserId(userId, cursor, limit = 20, game) {\n1208\t      const effectiveLimit = Math.min(limit, 50);\n1209\t      const cursorFilter = cursor ? sql`AND t.id < ${cursor}` : sql``;\n1210\t      const gameFilter = game ? sql`AND t.game = ${game}` : sql``;\n1211\t      const rows = await sql<Transaction[]>`\n1212\t        SELECT t.*\n1213\t        FROM transactions t\n1214\t        JOIN player_profiles p ON p.wallet = t.wallet\n1215\t        WHERE p.user_id = ${userId}\n1216\t          ${cursorFilter}\n1217\t          ${gameFilter}\n1218\t        ORDER BY t.id DESC\n1219\t        LIMIT ${effectiveLimit}\n1220\t      `;\n1221\t      return rows.map(normalizeTransaction);\n1222\t    },\n1223\t\n1224\t    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01C2Pn5rKeJTogFTCp3dWYsS","session_id":"2e700c10-4389-4a9a-beb2-50db732591da","uuid":"d54fabb4-9da0-4728-8def-febf96d9e51d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:51:40.749Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ThYtB88PUgPs9vxKcMn6Rv","type":"tool_result","content":"649\t### FR-14: Player-Facing API Endpoints\n650\t\n651\tAPI for the frontend to display challenges, progress, points, and crate history.\n652\t\n653\tPlayer-facing note: all challenge and reward updates are async from `game.settled`. Progress, points, and crate history should appear within seconds after settlement, but are not guaranteed to be visible in the same request path that triggered settlement.\n654\t\n655\t**Endpoints:**\n656\t\n657\t| Method | Path | Description |\n658\t|---|---|---|\n659\t| `GET` | `/challenges/mine` | Returns active + recently completed challenges for the authenticated user. Triggers lazy assignment if needed. |\n660\t| `GET` | `/challenges/mine/history` | Paginated list of past challenge completions |\n661\t| `GET` | `/points/mine` | Returns current point balance and lifetime earned |\n662\t| `GET` | `/points/mine/history` | Paginated points ledger history from `point_grants` |\n663\t| `GET` | `/crates/mine` | Paginated crate drop history with `status` (`pending`, `granted`, `failed`) |\n664\t| `GET` | `/dogpile/current` | Returns current/next Dogpile event (if any) with countdown to start or end |\n665\t| `GET` | `/dogpile/schedule` | Returns upcoming Dogpile events |\n666\t\n667\t**`GET /challenges/mine` response shape:**\n668\t```typescript\n669\t{\n670\t  daily: {\n671\t    challenges: Array<{\n672\t      id: number;\n673\t      title: string;\n674\t      description: string;\n675\t      progress: number;\n676\t      target: number;\n677\t      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n678\t      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n679\t      completedAt: string | null;\n680\t    }>;\n681\t    bonus: {\n682\t      title: string;\n683\t      required: number;\n684\t      completed: number;\n685\t      status: \"active\" | \"completed\";\n686\t      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n687\t    } | null;\n688\t    resetsAt: string;  // ISO 8601\n689\t  };\n690\t  weekly: {\n691\t    /* same shape; `bonus` is `null` in M1 unless a weekly completion bonus is explicitly configured */\n692\t  };\n693\t  onboarding: {\n694\t    steps: Array<{ /* same shape + locked: boolean */ }>;\n695\t    completed: boolean;\n696\t  } | null;  // null after onboarding complete\n697\t}\n698\t```\n699\t\n700\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n701\t- [ ] `GET /challenges/mine` returns daily, weekly, and onboarding sections\n702\t- [ ] Lazy assignment triggered on first call after daily/weekly reset\n703\t- [ ] Response includes progress, target, status, reward, and reset countdown\n704\t- [ ] Onboarding section shows locked steps (prerequisite not yet met) with `locked: true`\n705\t- [ ] Onboarding section is `null` for players who completed all onboarding steps\n706\t- [ ] `GET /points/mine` returns `{ balance, lifetimeEarned }`\n707\t- [ ] `GET /points/mine/history` returns paginated point grant rows with source metadata and timestamps from `point_grants`\n708\t- [ ] `GET /challenges/mine/history` returns paginated past completions\n709\t- [ ] `GET /crates/mine` returns paginated crate drops with type, amount, timestamp, and payout status semantics (`pending` queued, `granted` applied, `failed` needs retry/manual review)\n710\t- [ ] `GET /dogpile/current` returns active event with countdown to `ends_at`, or next scheduled event with countdown to `starts_at`\n711\t- [ ] All endpoints require JWT auth (existing middleware)\n712\t- [ ] All endpoints use standard error format (existing `errorResponse` helper)\n713\t\n714\t---\n715\t\n716\t### FR-15: Admin API Endpoints\n717\t\n718\tInternal endpoints for operators to manage campaigns, challenges, Dogpile events, and reward tuning. Fraud review and richer analytics are deferred until the lightweight M1 loop proves useful.\n719\t\n720\t| Method | Path | Description |\n721\t|---|---|---|\n722\t| `POST` | `/admin/campaigns` | Create a campaign |\n723\t| `PUT` | `/admin/campaigns/:id` | Update campaign (toggle active, change dates) |\n724\t| `POST` | `/admin/challenges` | Create a challenge template in a campaign |\n725\t| `PUT` | `/admin/challenges/:id` | Update challenge (toggle active, change threshold/reward) |\n726\t| `POST` | `/admin/dogpile` | Schedule a Dogpile event |\n727\t| `PUT` | `/admin/dogpile/:id` | Update/cancel a Dogpile event |\n728\t| `GET` | `/admin/dogpile` | List all Dogpile events |\n729\t| `PUT` | `/admin/reward-config/:key` | Update a reward config value |\n730\t| `GET` | `/admin/reward-config` | List all reward config values |\n731\t| `GET` | `/admin/reward-pool` | Reward pool balance and lifetime stats |\n732\t\n733\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n734\t- [ ] All admin endpoints require operator-level auth\n735\t- [ ] Campaign CRUD: create, update, toggle active. Cannot delete (soft-disable only).\n736\t- [ ] Challenge CRUD: create, update, toggle active within a campaign\n737\t- [ ] Dogpile scheduling: create events, cancel future events, cannot modify active events\n738\t- [ ] Reward config: read all, update by key\n739\t- [ ] Reward pool: read current balance, lifetime funded, lifetime paid\n740\t\n741\t---\n742\t\n743\t## Success Criteria\n744\t\n745\t1. A player who plays 5 coinflip games in a day sees their \"Play 5 games\" daily challenge progress from 0/5 to 5/5 and transition to completed — without any manual action.\n746\t2. A player who completes all 3 daily challenges receives a bonus crate.\n747\t3. A new player who has never played sees onboarding challenges guiding them through their first games.\n748\t4. Points accumulate proportionally to wagered volume across all games.\n749\t5. SOL crate payouts are capped and recorded by reward-pool accounting and never exceed the pool balance.\n750\t6. During a Dogpile event, points earned per game are doubled (or per configured multiplier).\n751\t7. A refunded round does not advance challenges, points, or crate drops.\n752\t8. An operator can change the points-per-dollar rate and see it take effect on the next settled game.\n753\t\n754\t---\n755\t\n756\t## Dependencies & Assumptions\n757\t\n758\t**Dependencies:**\n759\t- Async event queue (spec 301) — operational, used for event routing\n760\t- Settlement workers — operational for all 3 games, need `game.settled` event emission added\n761\t- Existing `/price/sol` endpoint — used for USD conversion in points calculation\n762\t- JWT auth — used for player-facing endpoints\n763\t- Treasury-managed payout wallet — used for SOL crate payouts (same pattern as referral claims)\n764\t\n765\t**Assumptions:**\n766\t- SOL/USD price is reasonably fresh (Close Call already depends on this)\n767\t- Game volume is sufficient to fund the reward pool meaningfully (if not, seed the pool manually)\n768\t- Frontend team will consume the API contract defined in FR-14 (we don't build the UI)\n769\t- M1 uses fixed daily/weekly challenge selection (same for all players). Pool rotation is M2.\n770\t\n771\t---\n772\t\n773\t## Validation Plan\n774\t\n775\t| Criterion | Method | Evidence |\n776\t|---|---|---|\n777\t| Points awarded correctly | Integration test: settle game, check `point_grants` + `player_points` | Test output |\n778\t| SOL crate accounting debits pool correctly | Integration test: settle game with mock RNG, verify `reward_pool_fundings` + pool decrement | Test output |\n779\t| Dogpile multiplier applies | Integration test: settle game during active Dogpile, verify 2x points | Test output |\n780\t| Refunded rounds are excluded | Integration test: process refunded settlement, verify no progress, no points, no crates | Test output |\n781\t| Challenge progress automatic | Integration test: settle game, verify assignment.progress incremented | Test output |\n782\t| Completion bonus triggers | Integration test: complete 3 dailies, verify bonus_completions row | Test output |\n783\t| Onboarding chain sequential | Integration test: complete step 1, verify step 2 assigned | Test output |\n784\t| Idempotency | Integration test: process same logical round twice (duplicate enqueue / replay), verify no duplicate progress, grants, crates, or pool funding | Test output |\n785\t| Config changes live | Integration test: update config, settle game, verify new config applied | Test output |\n786\t| Pool can't go negative | Integration test: drain pool, verify SOL crate suppressed | Test output |\n787\t| API returns correct shape | Integration test: call `/challenges/mine`, verify response schema | Test output |\n788\t| Points history is auditable | Integration test: award points from wager + crate + challenge completion, verify `/points/mine/history` ledger rows | Test output |\n789\t\n790\t---\n791\t\n792\t## Design Decisions & Review Notes\n793\t\n794\tTightenings applied during spec review (2026-04-03). Rationale for each:\n795\t\n796\t### 1. `progress_events.metadata` JSONB column added (FR-2)\n797\tThe `unique_game_types` condition requires knowing which game types have already been counted for an assignment. Without metadata, the adapter would need to join back to round data via `round_id` on every evaluation — fragile and slow. Storing `{\"game\":\"coinflip\"}` in the progress event lets the adapter query `SELECT DISTINCT metadata->>'game' FROM progress_events WHERE assignment_id = ?` directly. This is in the M1 critical path (onboarding step 3 and weekly \"play every game type\" both use `unique_game_types`).\n798\t\n799\t### 2. `challenges.scope` CHECK constraint added (FR-2)\n800\tWithout validation, a typo like `'coinflp'` in seed data or admin API would silently create a challenge that never matches any settled game. The CHECK constraint (`scope IN ('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')`) catches this at insert time. When new game types ship, the constraint must be extended via migration — an acceptable cost vs silent misconfiguration.\n801\t\n802\t### 3. `challenges.eligible_if` JSONB column added (FR-2)\n803\tThe reference spec defined `EligibilityRule` (min_heat_tier, min_games_played) as a first-class entity. M1 doesn't need eligibility gating, but adding a JSONB column now is zero runtime cost and avoids a schema migration once targeted challenges are needed in M2. The engine ignores it in M1 (empty object = no rules). When eligibility logic is implemented, it reads this field — no DDL change required.\n804\t\n805\t### 4. Deterministic challenge selection rule specified (FR-11)\n806\t\"All players get the same 3\" was underspecified — without a defined selection rule, two players calling `/challenges/mine` at different times could get different assignments if the active pool changed between requests. Selection is now explicitly `ORDER BY sort_order ASC LIMIT N` from active challenges. This is deterministic, operator-controllable via the admin API (reorder to rotate which challenges are live), and trivially replaceable with a seed-based random draw when pool rotation ships in M2.\n807\t\n808\t### 5. Template deactivation policy documented (FR-11)\n809\tAdmin could deactivate a challenge template while players have live assignments for it. Without a stated policy, implementations might auto-expire those assignments (losing player progress) or leave them in a broken state. Policy: deactivating a template does not affect existing assignments. Players finish their current period; the deactivated template simply won't be selected for future periods.\n810\t\n811\t### 6. Pool row-lock requirement made explicit (FR-4, FR-5)\n812\tSOL crate payout reads the pool balance, calculates a percentage, and decrements. If two `crate.drop` events are processed concurrently (the event queue claims batches of 10), both could read the same balance and overspend. While the current queue processes events serially per worker, this is an implementation detail — the spec should not assume it. Requiring `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` on the `reward_pool` singleton before balance reads makes the invariant (pool never goes negative) hold regardless of concurrency model.\n813\t\n814\t### 7. Event naming convention note\n815\tThe spec uses dot-notation in prose (`game.settled`, `reward.pool_fund`) and SCREAMING_SNAKE in the implementation checklist (`GAME_SETTLED`, `REWARD_POOL_FUND`). Reviewed and confirmed consistent: SCREAMING_SNAKE is the TypeScript constant name, dot-notation is the logical event type string stored in the queue. This matches the existing codebase pattern (`REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED` constant → `referral.code_applied` type string). No change needed.\n816\t\n817\t### Known M2 migration points\n818\tThese are deliberate M1 scoping decisions, not oversights:\n819\t\n820\t| Future need | M1 state | Migration path |\n821\t|---|---|---|\n822\t| Multi-condition challenges | Single action per challenge | Add `challenge_steps` table, update evaluation engine |\n823\t| Pool rotation (per-player dailies) | `sort_order`-based fixed selection | Swap selection function to seed-based random draw |\n824\t| Streak / volume conditions | Only `count` + `unique_game_types` | New adapter + condition evaluator branch |\n825\t| KOL-triggered challenges | No attribution scoping | Campaign-level scoping + KOL dashboard |\n826\t| Flash quests / ephemeral | No real-time push | Push notification infra + ephemeral campaign type |\n827\t\n828\t---\n829\t\n830\t## Completion Signal\n831\t\n832\t### Implementation Checklist\n833\t\n834\tEach item is one autonomous iteration (one `claude -p` invocation). Tests are bundled with the feature they verify. Items are ordered by dependency — execute top to bottom.\n835\t\n836\t**Phase 0: Event Plumbing**\n837\t\n838\t- [x] [backend] Add `GAME_SETTLED`, `REWARD_POOL_FUND`, `POINTS_GRANT`, `CRATE_DROP`, `CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT` event types to `event-types.ts`. Emit `game.settled` event in `settle-tx.ts` within the existing settlement DB transaction for both coinflip and lord (jackpot) rounds — payload must match FR-1 schema (roundId, roundPda, game, players[], feeLamports, settledAt). Integration test: settle a coinflip round, verify `game.settled` event row in `event_queue` with correct payload shape; duplicate settlement retry produces duplicate event rows safely. Verify: `cd backend && pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test` (FR-1) (done: iteration 1)\n839\t\n840\t- [x] [backend] Emit `game.settled` event in `closecall-clock.ts` within the closecall settlement transaction — same payload schema as FR-1 with `game: \"closecall\"`. Integration test: settle a closecall round, verify event row in queue with correct payload. Verify: `cd backend && pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test` (FR-1) (done: iteration 2)\n841\t\n842\t**Phase 1: Data Model & Seeds**\n843\t\n844\t- [x] [backend] Create migration `011_challenge_engine.sql` with all tables from FR-2: `reward_config`, `player_points`, `point_grants`, `reward_pool`, `reward_pool_fundings`, `campaigns`, `challenges` (with `scope` CHECK constraint and `eligible_if` JSONB column), `challenge_assignments`, `progress_events` (with `metadata` JSONB column), `completion_bonuses`, `bonus_completions`, `crate_drops`, `fraud_flags`, `dogpile_events`. Seed `reward_config` with all FR-13 defaults. Seed `reward_pool` singleton (balance 0). Seed campaigns: daily, weekly, onboarding. Seed ~6 daily challenge templates + ~4 weekly challenge templates (from FR-11 examples, ordered by `sort_order`). Seed 3 onboarding challenge templates with `prerequisite_id` chain (FR-12). Seed daily completion bonus (required_count=3, reward_type='crate'). Test: migration runs cleanly on fresh DB, all seeds present, foreign keys enforced, UNIQUE constraints verified. Verify: `cd backend && pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test` (FR-2, FR-9, FR-11, FR-12, FR-13) (done: iteration 3)\n845\t\n846\t**Phase 2: Reward Handlers**\n847\t\n848\t- [x] [backend] Implement `quest_eligible(event, player)` function: returns `false` when `isWinner === null` (refunded game), `true` otherwise. Implement adapter registry (Map from action string to adapter function). Implement 3 M1 adapters matching the `VerificationAdapter` interface from FR-7: `game_completed` (returns `shouldProgress: true` when game matches `scope` or scope='any'), `game_won` (additionally requires `isWinner === true`), `lobby_filled` (requires `isCreator === true`). Unknown action types log warning and return `shouldProgress: false`. Unit tests: each adapter with scope='any' and scope-specific cases; refund exclusion via quest_eligible; unknown adapter type. Verify: `cd backend && pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test` (FR-7, FR-10) (done: iteration 4)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TLRvQa8LiFx2Z5CcFD9NBy","session_id":"2e700c10-4389-4a9a-beb2-50db732591da","uuid":"113c0dae-8b64-4b92-8d6f-5c6bdd5f221c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:51:40.914Z"}
