{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TLRvQa8LiFx2Z5CcFD9NBy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile all the information you requested. Here's a comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Database Schema Report\n\n### 1. **player_points Table Schema** (migration 011)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE player_points (\n  user_id             TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  balance             BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  lifetime_earned     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Stores the current point balance and lifetime statistics for each player. Single row per user, updated atomically when points are granted.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **point_grants Table Schema** (migration 011)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE point_grants (\n  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source_type IN ('wager', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed', 'crate_points')),\n  source_id           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_point_grants_user_created ON point_grants (user_id, created_at DESC);\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Immutable append-only ledger of point grants (source of truth for history and idempotency). The UNIQUE constraint on `(user_id, source_type, source_id)` provides idempotency — duplicate grants for the same logical source are prevented.\n\n**source_type options:**\n- `'wager'` — points from game settlement (proportional to wagered volume)\n- `'challenge_completed'` — points from completing a challenge template\n- `'bonus_completed'` — points from completing a completion bonus\n- `'crate_points'` — points from opening a points crate\n\n---\n\n### 3. **crate_drops Table Schema** (migration 011)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE crate_drops (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  trigger_type    TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (trigger_type IN ('game_settled', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed')),\n  trigger_id      TEXT NOT NULL,\n  crate_type      TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (crate_type IN ('points', 'sol')),\n  contents_amount TEXT NOT NULL,\n  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'granted', 'failed')),\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  granted_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_crate_drops_user ON crate_drops (user_id, created_at DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_crate_drops_pending ON crate_drops (status) WHERE status = 'pending';\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Records loot crate drops triggered by games, challenge completions, or bonus completions. Crates can be either point drops or SOL payouts from the reward pool.\n\n**Fields:**\n- `trigger_type`: What event triggered the drop (`'game_settled'`, `'challenge_completed'`, `'bonus_completed'`)\n- `trigger_id`: The round_id, challenge_id, or bonus_id that triggered it (used for idempotency)\n- `crate_type`: `'points'` or `'sol'`\n- `contents_amount`: Stringified amount (in the currency of crate_type)\n- `status`: `'pending'` (queued), `'granted'` (applied to user), `'failed'` (retry/manual review)\n- UNIQUE constraint on `(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)` prevents duplicate crate drops for the same event\n\n---\n\n## FR-14 API Response Shapes\n\n### **GET /challenges/mine** (Response Shape from spec lines 668–697)\n\n```typescript\n{\n  daily: {\n    challenges: Array<{\n      id: number;\n      title: string;\n      description: string;\n      progress: number;\n      target: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n      completedAt: string | null;  // ISO 8601 timestamp or null\n    }>;\n    bonus: {\n      title: string;\n      required: number;\n      completed: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n    } | null;\n    resetsAt: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp of next daily reset (00:00 UTC)\n  };\n  \n  weekly: {\n    challenges: Array<{\n      id: number;\n      title: string;\n      description: string;\n      progress: number;\n      target: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n      completedAt: string | null;\n    }>;\n    bonus: null;  // No weekly bonus in M1\n    resetsAt: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp of next weekly reset (Monday 00:00 UTC)\n  };\n  \n  onboarding: {\n    steps: Array<{\n      id: number;\n      title: string;\n      description: string;\n      progress: number;\n      target: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n      completedAt: string | null;\n      locked: boolean;  // true if prerequisite not yet completed\n    }>;\n    completed: boolean;  // true if all steps finished\n  } | null;  // null after onboarding is complete\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /points/mine** (Response Shape)\n\n```typescript\n{\n  balance: number;  // Current point balance (BIGINT from player_points.balance)\n  lifetimeEarned: number;  // Cumulative points earned (BIGINT from player_points.lifetime_earned)\n}\n```\n\nReturns `{ balance: 0, lifetimeEarned: 0 }` if no `player_points` row exists for the user.\n\n---\n\n### **GET /points/mine/history** (Response Shape)\n\nPaginated list of `point_grants` rows ordered DESC by `created_at`:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  data: Array<{\n    id: number;\n    source_type: \"wager\" | \"challenge_completed\" | \"bonus_completed\" | \"crate_points\";\n    source_id: string;  // The round_id, challenge_id, bonus_id, or crate_id\n    amount: number;\n    metadata: Record<string, any>;  // JSONB field from point_grants\n    created_at: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp\n  }>;\n  // pagination fields (cursor or offset+limit TBD by implementation)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /crates/mine** (Response Shape)\n\nPaginated list of `crate_drops` rows ordered DESC by `created_at`:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  data: Array<{\n    id: number;\n    crate_type: \"points\" | \"sol\";\n    contents_amount: string;  // The amount as stored in the DB (may be stringified)\n    status: \"pending\" | \"granted\" | \"failed\";\n    created_at: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp\n    granted_at: string | null;  // ISO 8601 timestamp when status changed to 'granted', or null\n  }>;\n  // pagination fields (cursor or offset+limit TBD by implementation)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /dogpile/current** (Response Shape)\n\n```typescript\n{\n  id: number;\n  status: \"active\" | \"scheduled\";  // Priority: active > next-scheduled\n  multiplier: number;  // e.g. 2.0\n  starts_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  ends_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  countdown_ms?: number;  // Optional: ms until starts_at (if scheduled) or ends_at (if active)\n} | null  // null if no active or upcoming dogpile event\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /dogpile/schedule** (Response Shape)\n\nOrdered list of upcoming `dogpile_events` rows:\n\n```typescript\nArray<{\n  id: number;\n  status: \"scheduled\" | \"active\";\n  multiplier: number;\n  starts_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  ends_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  countdown_ms?: number;  // ms until starts_at or ends_at\n}>  // Ordered by starts_at ASC\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration Test Patterns (from integration.test.ts)\n\nFrom the last 200 lines of the integration test file, here are the key test patterns used:\n\n1. **Setup/Teardown**:\n   - `beforeAll`: Initialize `rawSql` (SQL client), `db` (Db instance), and Hono app with JWT middleware\n   - `afterAll`: Close DB and SQL connections\n   - `beforeEach`: TRUNCATE all relevant tables and reset `reward_pool` singleton to 0\n\n2. **Database Truncation Pattern**:\n   ```typescript\n   await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, closecall_rounds, ..., RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`;\n   ```\n\n3. **JWT Token Generation**:\n   ```typescript\n   const token = await makeJwt(testWallet, testUserId);\n   // Then use in request headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }\n   ```\n\n4. **HTTP Request Testing**:\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await app.request(\"/path\", {\n     method: \"GET\",\n     headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n   const body = (await res.json()) as Record<string, any>;\n   ```\n\n5. **Direct SQL Assertions**:\n   ```typescript\n   const results = await rawSql<{ field1: string; field2: number }[]>`\n     SELECT field1, field2 FROM table_name WHERE condition = ${value}\n   `;\n   expect(results[0]!.field1).toBe(\"expected\");\n   ```\n\n6. **Idempotency Testing**:\n   - Process the same event twice\n   - Verify UNIQUE constraints prevent duplicates (via `progress_events.UNIQUE(assignment_id, round_id)`)\n   - Verify `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on assignments prevents double-creation\n\n7. **Response Shape Validation**:\n   ```typescript\n   for (const ch of body.daily.challenges) {\n     expect(ch).toHaveProperty(\"id\");\n     expect(ch).toHaveProperty(\"title\");\n     // ... validate each field\n   }\n   ```\n\n8. **Period Key Computations**:\n   ```typescript\n   const dailyKey = dailyPeriodKey();  // Returns \"YYYY-MM-DD\"\n   const weeklyKey = weeklyPeriodKey();  // Returns \"YYYY-WNN\"\n   ```\n\n---\n\n**File Paths for Reference:**\n- Migration: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql`\n- Spec: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/400-challenge-engine/spec.md` (FR-14 starts at line 649)\n- Integration tests: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` (GET /challenges/mine tests at line 2424+)"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e700c10-4389-4a9a-beb2-50db732591da","uuid":"c8458863-ba4a-4e46-bc3d-0ebc4197efc5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:52:09.280Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the DB schema and test patterns in /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/. I need:\n1. The player_points table schema from migration 011\n2. The point_grants table schema from migration 011\n3. The crate_drops table schema from migration 011\n4. The integration test file to see existing test patterns\n\nRead these files:\n- /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql (search for player_points, point_grants, crate_drops table definitions)\n- /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts (last 200 lines for test patterns)\n\nAlso check what the FR-14 section of the spec says about these endpoints:\n- /workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/400-challenge-engine/spec.md (search for FR-14)\n\nReport back with the full table schemas for player_points, point_grants, crate_drops, and the FR-14 API response shapes.","agentId":"abd37292b27194d48","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile all the information you requested. Here's a comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Database Schema Report\n\n### 1. **player_points Table Schema** (migration 011)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE player_points (\n  user_id             TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  balance             BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  lifetime_earned     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Stores the current point balance and lifetime statistics for each player. Single row per user, updated atomically when points are granted.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **point_grants Table Schema** (migration 011)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE point_grants (\n  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source_type IN ('wager', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed', 'crate_points')),\n  source_id           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_point_grants_user_created ON point_grants (user_id, created_at DESC);\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Immutable append-only ledger of point grants (source of truth for history and idempotency). The UNIQUE constraint on `(user_id, source_type, source_id)` provides idempotency — duplicate grants for the same logical source are prevented.\n\n**source_type options:**\n- `'wager'` — points from game settlement (proportional to wagered volume)\n- `'challenge_completed'` — points from completing a challenge template\n- `'bonus_completed'` — points from completing a completion bonus\n- `'crate_points'` — points from opening a points crate\n\n---\n\n### 3. **crate_drops Table Schema** (migration 011)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE crate_drops (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  trigger_type    TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (trigger_type IN ('game_settled', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed')),\n  trigger_id      TEXT NOT NULL,\n  crate_type      TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (crate_type IN ('points', 'sol')),\n  contents_amount TEXT NOT NULL,\n  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'granted', 'failed')),\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  granted_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_crate_drops_user ON crate_drops (user_id, created_at DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_crate_drops_pending ON crate_drops (status) WHERE status = 'pending';\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Records loot crate drops triggered by games, challenge completions, or bonus completions. Crates can be either point drops or SOL payouts from the reward pool.\n\n**Fields:**\n- `trigger_type`: What event triggered the drop (`'game_settled'`, `'challenge_completed'`, `'bonus_completed'`)\n- `trigger_id`: The round_id, challenge_id, or bonus_id that triggered it (used for idempotency)\n- `crate_type`: `'points'` or `'sol'`\n- `contents_amount`: Stringified amount (in the currency of crate_type)\n- `status`: `'pending'` (queued), `'granted'` (applied to user), `'failed'` (retry/manual review)\n- UNIQUE constraint on `(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)` prevents duplicate crate drops for the same event\n\n---\n\n## FR-14 API Response Shapes\n\n### **GET /challenges/mine** (Response Shape from spec lines 668–697)\n\n```typescript\n{\n  daily: {\n    challenges: Array<{\n      id: number;\n      title: string;\n      description: string;\n      progress: number;\n      target: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n      completedAt: string | null;  // ISO 8601 timestamp or null\n    }>;\n    bonus: {\n      title: string;\n      required: number;\n      completed: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n    } | null;\n    resetsAt: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp of next daily reset (00:00 UTC)\n  };\n  \n  weekly: {\n    challenges: Array<{\n      id: number;\n      title: string;\n      description: string;\n      progress: number;\n      target: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n      completedAt: string | null;\n    }>;\n    bonus: null;  // No weekly bonus in M1\n    resetsAt: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp of next weekly reset (Monday 00:00 UTC)\n  };\n  \n  onboarding: {\n    steps: Array<{\n      id: number;\n      title: string;\n      description: string;\n      progress: number;\n      target: number;\n      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n      completedAt: string | null;\n      locked: boolean;  // true if prerequisite not yet completed\n    }>;\n    completed: boolean;  // true if all steps finished\n  } | null;  // null after onboarding is complete\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /points/mine** (Response Shape)\n\n```typescript\n{\n  balance: number;  // Current point balance (BIGINT from player_points.balance)\n  lifetimeEarned: number;  // Cumulative points earned (BIGINT from player_points.lifetime_earned)\n}\n```\n\nReturns `{ balance: 0, lifetimeEarned: 0 }` if no `player_points` row exists for the user.\n\n---\n\n### **GET /points/mine/history** (Response Shape)\n\nPaginated list of `point_grants` rows ordered DESC by `created_at`:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  data: Array<{\n    id: number;\n    source_type: \"wager\" | \"challenge_completed\" | \"bonus_completed\" | \"crate_points\";\n    source_id: string;  // The round_id, challenge_id, bonus_id, or crate_id\n    amount: number;\n    metadata: Record<string, any>;  // JSONB field from point_grants\n    created_at: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp\n  }>;\n  // pagination fields (cursor or offset+limit TBD by implementation)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /crates/mine** (Response Shape)\n\nPaginated list of `crate_drops` rows ordered DESC by `created_at`:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  data: Array<{\n    id: number;\n    crate_type: \"points\" | \"sol\";\n    contents_amount: string;  // The amount as stored in the DB (may be stringified)\n    status: \"pending\" | \"granted\" | \"failed\";\n    created_at: string;  // ISO 8601 timestamp\n    granted_at: string | null;  // ISO 8601 timestamp when status changed to 'granted', or null\n  }>;\n  // pagination fields (cursor or offset+limit TBD by implementation)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /dogpile/current** (Response Shape)\n\n```typescript\n{\n  id: number;\n  status: \"active\" | \"scheduled\";  // Priority: active > next-scheduled\n  multiplier: number;  // e.g. 2.0\n  starts_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  ends_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  countdown_ms?: number;  // Optional: ms until starts_at (if scheduled) or ends_at (if active)\n} | null  // null if no active or upcoming dogpile event\n```\n\n---\n\n### **GET /dogpile/schedule** (Response Shape)\n\nOrdered list of upcoming `dogpile_events` rows:\n\n```typescript\nArray<{\n  id: number;\n  status: \"scheduled\" | \"active\";\n  multiplier: number;\n  starts_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  ends_at: string;  // ISO 8601\n  countdown_ms?: number;  // ms until starts_at or ends_at\n}>  // Ordered by starts_at ASC\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration Test Patterns (from integration.test.ts)\n\nFrom the last 200 lines of the integration test file, here are the key test patterns used:\n\n1. **Setup/Teardown**:\n   - `beforeAll`: Initialize `rawSql` (SQL client), `db` (Db instance), and Hono app with JWT middleware\n   - `afterAll`: Close DB and SQL connections\n   - `beforeEach`: TRUNCATE all relevant tables and reset `reward_pool` singleton to 0\n\n2. **Database Truncation Pattern**:\n   ```typescript\n   await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, closecall_rounds, ..., RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`;\n   ```\n\n3. **JWT Token Generation**:\n   ```typescript\n   const token = await makeJwt(testWallet, testUserId);\n   // Then use in request headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }\n   ```\n\n4. **HTTP Request Testing**:\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await app.request(\"/path\", {\n     method: \"GET\",\n     headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n   const body = (await res.json()) as Record<string, any>;\n   ```\n\n5. **Direct SQL Assertions**:\n   ```typescript\n   const results = await rawSql<{ field1: string; field2: number }[]>`\n     SELECT field1, field2 FROM table_name WHERE condition = ${value}\n   `;\n   expect(results[0]!.field1).toBe(\"expected\");\n   ```\n\n6. **Idempotency Testing**:\n   - Process the same event twice\n   - Verify UNIQUE constraints prevent duplicates (via `progress_events.UNIQUE(assignment_id, round_id)`)\n   - Verify `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on assignments prevents double-creation\n\n7. **Response Shape Validation**:\n   ```typescript\n   for (const ch of body.daily.challenges) {\n     expect(ch).toHaveProperty(\"id\");\n     expect(ch).toHaveProperty(\"title\");\n     // ... validate each field\n   }\n   ```\n\n8. **Period Key Computations**:\n   ```typescript\n   const dailyKey = dailyPeriodKey();  // Returns \"YYYY-MM-DD\"\n   const weeklyKey = weeklyPeriodKey();  // Returns \"YYYY-WNN\"\n   ```\n\n---\n\n**File Paths for Reference:**\n- Migration: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql`\n- Spec: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/400-challenge-engine/spec.md` (FR-14 starts at line 649)\n- Integration tests: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` (GET /challenges/mine tests at line 2424+)"}],"totalDurationMs":41470,"totalTokens":48211,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3405,"cache_read_input_tokens":41887,"output_tokens":2917,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3405},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
